To find (A x B) U (A x {5}), we first need to find the Cartesian products A x B and A x {5}.

A x B = {(a, b) | a ∈ A, b ∈ B} = {(1, 2), (1, 4), (2, 2), (2, 4), (3, 2), (3, 4)}

A x {5} = {(a, b) | a ∈ A, b ∈ {5}} = {(1, 5), (2, 5), (3, 5)}

Now, we find the union of these two sets:

(A x B) U (A x {5}) = {(1, 2), (1, 4), (2, 2), (2, 4), (3, 2), (3, 4), (1, 5), (2, 5), (3, 5)}
